replies.msg:
Counter-attacking is what we do against Arsenal<br />
<br />
&ldquo;That&rsquo;s part of it. If you go through the history and the games we&rsquo;ve played against Arsenal that&rsquo;s how it is. I remember a goal I scored in 1997 after we defended a corner; it went from Giggsy to Karel [Poborsky] to Andy [Cole] and into me. Everyone knows about the classic Champions League goal [in 2009] with Ji [-sung Park], Cristiano [Ronaldo] and Wayne [Rooney] running forward. Wazza has scored a couple more like that, as has Ji, so <span style="color: red;">the counter-attacking threat that we have is in our history against Arsenal</span>.&rdquo;

